headline.main: Markets fall but no Greek panic yet
headline.sub: Markets fall but no Greek panic yet

lead_paragraph: Greece's deepening debt crisis prompted bankers to pause, but not panic, on Monday.  As David Pollard reports, euro zone stocks remained well ahead of where they were at the start of the year and while government borrowing costs shot up in Europe's indebted southern countries they remained well below the heights scaled at the peak of the crisis in 2011/2012.
